AU  - Wang, Yu-Peng
AU  - Ren, Jie
AU  - Gopalakrishnan, Sarang
AU  - Vasseur, Romain
TI  - Superdiffusive transport in chaotic quantum systems with nodal
  interactions
LA  - und
PY  - 2025
AB  - We introduce a class of interacting fermionic quantum models in $d$
dimensions with nodal interactions that exhibit superdiffusive transport. We
establish non-perturbatively that the nodal structure of the interactions gives
rise to long-lived quasiparticle excitations that result in a diverging
diffusion constant, even though the system is fully chaotic. Using a Boltzmann
equation approach, we find that the charge mode acquires an anomalous
dispersion relation at long wavelength $\omega(q) \sim q^{z} $ with dynamical
exponent $z={\rm min}[(2n+d)/2n,2]$, where $n$ is the order of the nodal point
in momentum space. We verify our predictions in one dimensional systems using
tensor-network techniques.
