AB  - The proceedings contain 31 papers. The topics discussed include: mobility prediction at the tactical edge: a handover for centralized/decentralized networks; detection of previously unknown advanced persistent threats through visual analytics with the MASFAD framework; coordinating the SDN and TDMA planes in software-defined tactical MANETs with adaptive coding and modulation; sub-block turbo equalization for CPM waveforms in multipath environments; comparison of transformer models for performance on domain specific texts: a systematic evaluation of intrinsic model performance; quantum computing application opportunities in military scenarios; enabling activity based intelligence with visual analytics; analysis of link performance degradation from interferences in military networks; and accelerating NATO transformation with SnTEE: experiments with network security function virtualization in coalition networks.
