AB  - The proceedings contain 9 papers. The topics discussed include: designing automatic railway switch heating system with innovative intelligent sensors; modeling and planning of parallel information processing in a computing system operating in extremely conditions; line-by-line prediction method in lossy image compression; study of the structural significance of supply chain elements with variable order rate; characteristics of ecosystems of quantum computing and prospects for their use in transport; analysis of algorithms for generating the matrix of coefficients of non-stationary queuing system models; domestic intelligent information and analytical platform and its use in transport; complex scheduling of measurement and calculation systems functioning; and on the survivability of infrastructure facilities in the arctic during fires.
