AB  - The proceedings contain 164 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Computer Science On-line. The topics include: Sector-Selective Hybrid Scheme Facilitating Hardware Supportability Over Image Compression; multicriteria Model for Evaluation of Outsourcing Services by Logistics Operators; HNM: Hexagonal Network Model for Comprehensive Smart City Management in Internet-of-Things; automated Extraction of Paradigmatic Relationships from Natural Language Texts on the Basis of the Complex of Heterogeneous Features; algorithmic and Software Support for Technological Decision-Making in the Process of Induction Soldering; development of the Architecture of the System for Detecting Objects in Images; development of a Method for Modeling Entangled Quantum Computations Applicable in the Simon’s Quantum Algorithm; search-Based Wrapper Feature Selection Methods in Software Defect Prediction: An Empirical Analysis; synthesis of Fuzzy Algorithms Controlling the Temperature of the Polymer in the Extruder; parallel Algorithm for K-Means Clustering in Wood Species Classification; eye-Tracking Study of Direction Influence of User’s Attention for Intelligence System Design; design and Software Implementation of Heuristic and Suboptimal Strategies for the Mancala/Kalah Game; methodology for Job Advertisements Analysis in the Labor Market in Metropolitan Cities: The Case Study of the Capital of Russia; statistical Analysis for Customer Product Reviews in Russian Internet Segment Using Text Mining; cycle-Breaking Approach to Reduce Inconsistency in Pairwise Comparisons; microPython as a Development Platform for IoT Applications; the Study of Optimization Method for Axisymmetric Aerodynamic Profile in the Gas Flow by Using Evolutionary Algorithms; modeling Business Process and Events; factors Influencing Acceptance of Technology by Senior Citizens: A Systematic Review; preface.
