AB  - The study of bulk properties of the system formed in heavy-ion collisions shed light on the evolution of the system with time. We present the results on energy and centrality dependence of particle yields and ratios using A Multi- Phase Transport Model (AMPT) and Ultrarelativistic Quantum Molecular Dynamics (UrQMD) models. The results are discussed for both string melting and default versions of the AMPT model. The comparison of model predictions with the published RHIC data are also presented.
