AB  - Probabilistic approximations have previously been shown to extend the ability of atomistic simulations to measure diffusivities of spherical diffusant molecules as small as 1.0 x 10-9 cm2/s. This model has been augmented to include non-spherical molecules by the explicit inclusion of rotational modes. Simulation times of a tenth of a microsecond for Carbon Dioxide in PDMS have been achieved with modest usage of computing resources. The techniques presented take advantage of advanced computing environments including MPI, pthreads, and CUDA/GPGPU resources at the Texas Advanced Computing Center.
