AB  - The understanding of the whole process of cracking propagation, as well as, the knowledge of the parameters that change around these failures is of great importance for the sizing of the structure components that are subjected to several external uploads. Our proposal here is to describe the cracking propagation process targeting the dynamic aspect. Thus, it will be done a new evaluation of a concrete beam, submitted to three-point bending test, proposed by Peterson [1]. Three different forms of the material constitutive diagram will be presented and, also discussed their influences on the results, regarding the dynamic aspects of the cracking process, as well as, speed, acceleration, change of cracking frame with time and energy spent. © Civil-Comp Press, 2010.
