AB  - Quantum entanglement is a quantum mechanical phenomenon with applications in various fields. This book includes research on the time travel hypothesis, in the context of general relativity, the fundamental importance in the open quantum systems theory of the border line between "system" and "environment" and its applications; and a scheme of ghost imaging and the physics behind it with two EPR states.
